Description: Length of each forewing 3.1–3.5 mm (n = 10). Specimens in alcohol with compound eyes black, legs and thorax brown, abdomen dark brown dorsally, pale yellow ventrally (
Figs 1f, 1g
). Forewings with apical forks II, III, IV, and V present, crossveins r , s and r-m linearly aligned; hind wings with forks II and V present, R 1 atrophied, R 2+3 ends at Sc ( Fig. 7a ).

Male genitalia:
Tergum IX divided into two strongly sclerotized lateral apical sclerites (a.s. in 
Fig. 1b
) and two mesal lobes (t.IX in 
Fig. 1b and 1c
); in lateral view (
Fig. 1a
) each apical sclerite approximately triangular with dorsal margin deeply concave; in mesal view posterior margin slightly oblique (a.s. in 
Fig. 1b
) with finger-like basal process ventromesally; mesal lobes of tergum IX setose, fused with each other basally in dorsal view. Sternum IX in lateral view (
Fig. 1a
) subrectangular, with anterior margin slightly convex, and posterior margin slightly sinuate. Preanal appendages large, in lateral view (
Fig. 1a
) each with apicodorsal angle produced into a blunt process, lateral side heavily setose apically, each fused basally with apical sclerites of tergum IX; in dorsal view (pre.app. in 
Fig. 1c
) each with base narrow and apex swollen and truncate; in ventral view (pre.app. in 
Fig. 1d
) somewhat clavate. Coxopodites (cox. in 
Fig. 1a
) subrectangular in lateral view, each with apicodorsal angle produced into narrow process (
Figs 1a, 1d
); in ventral view coxopodites fused with each other basally and each with finger-like apicolateral process directed posteromesad (cox. in 
Fig. 1d
); harpagones each elliptical in lateral view and platelike in ventral view (har. in 
Figs 1a, 1d
), in ventral view with base round and articulated with coxopodite and with its apex trifurcate: lateral fork finger-like, setose and directed posterolaterad, middle fork bare and acute and directed laterad, mesal fork bare and apically blunt and curved posterolaterad. Phallic apparatus in lateral view (
Fig. 1a
) with endotheca cylindrical, subapex curved dorsad; in ventral view (
Fig. 1d
) endotheca tapering from base to apex, distal end blunt.
